article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 80, Cal Poly-SLO 57
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. -- James Nunnally scored 17 of his 20 points in the first half as UC Santa Barbara raced to an 80-57 victory over Cal Poly San Luis Obispo Thursday night. Orlando Johnson had 18 points and nine rebounds, and Jaime Serna scored 12 points for the Gauchos (11-7, 6-2 Big West), who made 52 percent of their outside shots. Lorenzo Keeler led the Mustangs (8-11, 5-3) with 20 points. Cal Poly shot 35 percent from the field. UC Santa Barbara roared to a 38-18 halftime lead, holding Cal Poly scoreless for 6 1/2 minutes at one point in the first half. It was 17-14 midway through the half but the Mustangs scored just four more points before halftime while Nunnally scored 12 in the same stretch. With the score already 47-24, the Gauchos went on a 10-0 run early in the second half, and eventually led by 35 points.
